To find the height of the root node, we need to determine the longest path from the root node to any leaf node. This can be done by tracing the paths from the root to all possible leaf nodes and finding the maximum length.

From the input, it looks like a list of edges in a tree where each line represents an edge from one node to another (parent to child). The root node here is the node 'd' as it appears first on the left-hand side and does not have any parent.

The height of the tree will be the longest sequence of "->" from 'd' to a leaf node, indicated by a node that does not appear on the left-hand side of any "->".

According to your input, the longest path from 'd' to a leaf node is:
```
d->e->f->g->h->i->j->k
```

This path has 7 edges. Therefore, the height of the root node 'd' is 7.
